SIMPLE: nuzzle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nuzzle
<hw>Nuz"zle</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nuzzled</conjf>
<pr>(n⟦ucr⟧z"z'ld)</pr>;<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Nuzzling</conjf> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧z"zl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[See <er>Noursle</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To noursle or nurse; to foster; to bring up.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The people had been <qex>nuzzled</qex> in idolatry.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Perh. a corruption of <ets>nestle</ets>. Cf.
<er>Nustle</er>.]</ety> <def>To nestle; to house, as in a
nest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 988 --></p>

<p><ent>Nuzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nuzzle
<hw>Nuz"zle</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧z"z'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Dim. fr.
<ets>nose</ets>. See <er>Nozzle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To work
with the nose, like a swine in the mud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>nuzzling</qex> in his flank, the loving swine⟦br⟧
Sheathed, unaware, the tusk in his soft groin.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He charged through an army of lawyers, sometimes . . .
<qex>nuzzling</qex> like an eel in the mud.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To go with head poised like a swine, with nose
down.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sir Roger shook his ears, and <qex>nuzzled</qex> along.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <ety>[Cf. <er>Nuzzle</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, 2.]</ety>
<def>To hide the head, as a child in the mother's bosom; to
nestle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To loiter; to idle.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ny</ent>⟦br⟧
